Note: ===================================================================
Note: MATLAB TO HIR TRANSLATOR
Note: ===================================================================
Note: Translates the MATLAB AST produced by matlab_parser.runa into the
Note: canonical typed HIR (hir_nodes.runa) consumed by the Translation
Note: universal translation system.

Note: This translator targets the SAME typed-HIR contract used by the
Note: other model-1 frontends (r_to_hir, ruby_to_hir, scala_to_hir): it
Note: builds real HIR_* nodes via hir_create_* / hir_set_* / hir_add_*
Note: and the matching hir_to_matlab backend reconstructs MATLAB source by
Note: reading those nodes back through hir_get_* accessors. Producer and
Note: consumer share exactly this representation.

Note: The MATLAB parser emits an ASTNode struct (node_type, value, children,
Note: metadata) accessed through ast_node_type / ast_node_value /
Note: ast_node_child / ast_node_child_count. Node-type tags are the
Note: MatlabParser.MATLAB_* constants.

Note: Part of the Translation Translation System
Note: Location: compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/matlab/matlab_to_hir.runa
Note: ===================================================================

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir_nodes.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/matlab/matlab_parser.runa" as MatlabParser
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/matlab/matlab_lexer.runa" as MatlabLexer
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as ListCore

Note: ===================================================================
Note: OPERATOR MAPPING
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Maps a MATLAB binary-operator spelling to the closest HIR_OP_* tag. HIR has
no dedicated power tag, and matrix-vs-elementwise distinctions are not
representable in the operator enum, so the precise original spelling is
preserved separately as "matlab_operator" metadata on the binary node and
the backend prefers that string. This map exists so passes that only look
at the HIR op enum still see a meaningful arithmetic/relational category.
@End Reasoning
Process called "map_matlab_operator_to_hir" takes operator as Integer returns Integer:
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "+" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_ADD
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "-" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_SUBTRACT
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "*" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_MULTIPLY
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, ".*" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_MULTIPLY
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "/" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_DIVIDE
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "./" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_DIVIDE
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "\\" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_DIVIDE
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, ".\\" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_DIVIDE
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "^" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_MULTIPLY
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, ".^" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_MULTIPLY
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "==" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_EQUAL
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "~=" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_NOT_EQUAL
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "<" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_LESS_THAN
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "<=" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_LESS_EQUAL
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, ">" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_GREATER_THAN
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, ">=" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_GREATER_EQUAL
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "&&" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_LOGICAL_AND
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "||" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_LOGICAL_OR
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "&" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_BITWISE_AND
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "|" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_BITWISE_OR
    End If
    Return HIR.HIR_OP_ADD
End Process

@Reasoning:
Maps a MATLAB unary-operator spelling to an HIR_OP_* tag. The negation,
logical-not and identity-plus forms have direct HIR counterparts; the
original spelling is also preserved via metadata for exact reconstruction.
@End Reasoning
Process called "map_matlab_unary_operator_to_hir" takes operator as Integer returns Integer:
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "~" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_LOGICAL_NOT
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "+" is equal to 1:
        Return HIR.HIR_OP_ADD
    End If
    Return HIR.HIR_OP_NEGATE
End Process

@Reasoning:
Detects MATLAB's leading-dot element-wise operator family (.*, ./, .^, .\)
so translate_binary_expression can attach the "matlab_elementwise" flag
that the backend reads to re-emit the dot-prefixed spelling.
@End Reasoning
Process called "is_matlab_elementwise_operator" takes operator as Integer returns Integer:
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, ".*" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, "./" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, ".^" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with operator, ".\\" is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: NUMBER LITERAL CLASSIFICATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
MATLAB numeric literals are kept as their original source spelling by the
lexer (including decimal points, exponents and imaginary suffixes). HIR
distinguishes integer and float literals, so this predicate scans the
spelling for a '.', 'e'/'E' exponent, or an 'i'/'j' imaginary suffix to
decide whether to emit an HIR float literal (1) or integer literal (0).
@End Reasoning
Process called "matlab_number_is_float" takes text as Integer returns Integer:
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with text
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than length:
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, i
        If ch is equal to 46:
            Return 1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 101:
            Return 1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 69:
            Return 1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 105:
            Return 1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 106:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: MAIN TRANSLATION ENTRY POINT
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Top-level entry. Creates the HIR module, names it "matlab_module" for the
backend's documentation comment, and walks the MATLAB program's top-level
children. Function and class definitions become module declarations; a
script wrapper's statements are hoisted into a synthesized
"matlab_script_main" function so every statement lives inside a function as
HIR requires.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_matlab_to_hir" takes matlab_ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir_module be proc hir_create_module from HIR
    proc hir_set_module_name from HIR with hir_module, "matlab_module"

    If matlab_ast is equal to 0:
        Return hir_module
    End If

    Let node_type be proc ast_node_type from MatlabParser with matlab_ast
    If node_type is not equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_PROGRAM:
        Return hir_module
    End If

    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with matlab_ast
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with matlab_ast, i
        Let child_type be proc ast_node_type from MatlabParser with child

        If child_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_FUNCTION:
            Let hir_function be proc translate_function with child
            proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with hir_module, hir_function
        End If

        If child_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_CLASSDEF:
            Let hir_class be proc translate_classdef with child
            proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with hir_module, hir_class
        End If

        If child_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_SCRIPT:
            Let hir_main be proc translate_script with child
            proc hir_add_declaration from HIR with hir_module, hir_main
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return hir_module
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: SCRIPT TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
MATLAB scripts have no enclosing function. They are wrapped in a synthetic
"matlab_script_main" function whose body block contains the translated
top-level statements in source order, satisfying HIR's requirement that
all statements live within a function body.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_script" takes script_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir_function be proc hir_create_function from HIR
    proc hir_set_function_name from HIR with hir_function, "matlab_script_main"

    Let hir_body be proc hir_create_block from HIR
    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with script_node
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let stmt be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with script_node, i
        Let hir_stmt be proc translate_statement with stmt
        If hir_stmt is not equal to 0:
            proc hir_add_statement from HIR with hir_body, hir_stmt
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc hir_set_function_body from HIR with hir_function, hir_body
    Return hir_function
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: FUNCTION TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
The MATLAB parser stores the function name in the node value slot and lays
out the children as: an optional output-marker node (an identifier whose
value is "outputs" with the output names as its children) OR a single
output identifier, then an optional input-marker node (identifier valued
"inputs" with parameter identifiers as children), then the body
(MATLAB_SCRIPT). Output names are stored as comma-joined
"matlab_output_params" metadata for the backend's [a,b] = f(...) form and a
single output as "matlab_single_output"; input identifiers become HIR
parameters.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_function" takes func_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir_function be proc hir_create_function from HIR

    Let func_name be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with func_node
    proc hir_set_function_name from HIR with hir_function, func_name

    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with func_node
    Let body_node be 0

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with func_node, i
        Let child_type be proc ast_node_type from MatlabParser with child

        If child_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_SCRIPT:
            Set body_node to child
        Otherwise:
            Note: Identifier-typed marker: "outputs", "inputs", or a single output
            Let marker_value be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with child
            Let is_outputs be proc string_equals from StringCore with marker_value, "outputs"
            Let is_inputs be proc string_equals from StringCore with marker_value, "inputs"

            If is_outputs is equal to 1:
                proc translate_output_marker with child, hir_function
            Otherwise:
                If is_inputs is equal to 1:
                    proc translate_input_marker with child, hir_function
                Otherwise:
                    Note: Single-output identifier
                    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_function, "matlab_single_output", marker_value
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    If body_node is not equal to 0:
        Let hir_body be proc translate_script with body_node
        Note: translate_script returns a function; reuse just its block.
        Let inner_block be proc hir_get_function_body from HIR with hir_body
        proc hir_set_function_body from HIR with hir_function, inner_block
    Otherwise:
        Let empty_block be proc hir_create_block from HIR
        proc hir_set_function_body from HIR with hir_function, empty_block
    End If

    Return hir_function
End Process

@Reasoning:
Collects the multiple-output parameter names into a comma-joined string
stored as "matlab_output_params" metadata. The backend splits this back
into the "[a, b] = name(...)" output list. A comma+space separator is used
so the backend can reuse the same spelling without re-padding.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_output_marker" takes outputs_node as Integer, hir_function as Integer:
    Let count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with outputs_node
    Let joined be ""
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let out_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with outputs_node, i
        Let out_name be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with out_child
        If i is greater than 0:
            Set joined to proc string_concat from StringPrim with joined, ", "
        End If
        Set joined to proc string_concat from StringPrim with joined, out_name
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_function, "matlab_output_params", joined
End Process

@Reasoning:
Each MATLAB formal input becomes an HIR parameter named after the source
identifier. MATLAB is dynamically typed so no parameter type is attached;
later type-inference passes settle types from usage.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_input_marker" takes inputs_node as Integer, hir_function as Integer:
    Let count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with inputs_node
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let in_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with inputs_node, i
        Let in_name be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with in_child
        Let hir_param be proc hir_create_parameter from HIR
        proc hir_set_parameter_name from HIR with hir_param, in_name
        proc hir_add_parameter from HIR with hir_function, hir_param
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: CLASS DEFINITION TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Translates a MATLAB classdef to an HIR class. The parser stores the class
name in the value slot; an optional base-class identifier and the member
blocks (properties / methods / events / enumeration) follow as children.
Properties and enumeration values become HIR fields; methods become HIR
functions tagged "is_method"; events and the enumeration flag are recorded
as class metadata the backend re-expands.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_classdef" takes class_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir_class be proc hir_create_class from HIR

    Let class_name be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with class_node
    proc hir_set_class_name from HIR with hir_class, class_name

    Let child_count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with class_node
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with class_node, i
        Let child_type be proc ast_node_type from MatlabParser with child

        If child_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_PROPERTIES:
            proc translate_properties_block with child, hir_class
        End If
        If child_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_METHODS:
            proc translate_methods_block with child, hir_class
        End If
        If child_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_EVENTS:
            proc translate_events_block with child, hir_class
        End If
        If child_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_ENUMERATION:
            proc translate_enumeration_block with child, hir_class
        End If
        If child_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_IDENTIFIER:
            Note: Base-class reference "classdef Name < Base"
            Let base_name be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with child
            proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "matlab_base_class", base_name
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return hir_class
End Process

@Reasoning:
Each declared property becomes an HIR field of the class. MATLAB does not
require property types, so only the name is recorded.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_properties_block" takes props_node as Integer, hir_class as Integer:
    Let count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with props_node
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let prop_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with props_node, i
        Let prop_name be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with prop_child
        Let hir_field be proc hir_create_field from HIR
        proc hir_set_field_name from HIR with hir_field, prop_name
        proc hir_add_class_member from HIR with hir_class, hir_field
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Each method body is a MATLAB function; reusing translate_function keeps the
output/input/body handling identical to free functions. The resulting HIR
function is tagged "is_method" and added as a class member so the backend
emits it inside a methods block.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_methods_block" takes methods_node as Integer, hir_class as Integer:
    Let count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with methods_node
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let method_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with methods_node, i
        Let method_type be proc ast_node_type from MatlabParser with method_child
        If method_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_FUNCTION:
            Let hir_method be proc translate_function with method_child
            proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_method, "is_method", "1"
            proc hir_add_class_member from HIR with hir_class, hir_method
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
HIR has no native event concept, so the declared event names are joined
into "matlab_events" metadata on the class for the backend to re-emit as a
MATLAB events block.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_events_block" takes events_node as Integer, hir_class as Integer:
    Let count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with events_node
    Let joined be ""
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let event_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with events_node, i
        Let event_name be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with event_child
        If i is greater than 0:
            Set joined to proc string_concat from StringPrim with joined, ", "
        End If
        Set joined to proc string_concat from StringPrim with joined, event_name
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "matlab_events", joined
End Process

@Reasoning:
Enumeration values become HIR fields and the class is flagged
"matlab_enumeration" so the backend re-emits them inside an enumeration
block rather than a properties block.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_enumeration_block" takes enum_node as Integer, hir_class as Integer:
    Let count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with enum_node
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let enum_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with enum_node, i
        Let enum_name be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with enum_child
        Let hir_field be proc hir_create_field from HIR
        proc hir_set_field_name from HIR with hir_field, enum_name
        proc hir_add_class_member from HIR with hir_class, hir_field
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_class, "matlab_enumeration", "1"
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: STATEMENT TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Statement dispatcher. Maps each MATLAB statement AST type to an HIR
statement: control flow (if/for/while/switch/try), jumps (return/break/
continue), assignment, expression statements, and the global/persistent
declarations (lowered to flagged blocks). The SPMD and parfor variants are
expressed as flagged versions of their sequential analogues. Unknown types
return 0 and are skipped by callers.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_statement" takes stmt_node as Integer returns Integer:
    If stmt_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let stmt_type be proc ast_node_type from MatlabParser with stmt_node

    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_SCRIPT:
        Return proc translate_block with stmt_node
    End If
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_ASSIGN_STMT:
        Return proc translate_assignment with stmt_node
    End If
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_IF_STMT:
        Return proc translate_if with stmt_node
    End If
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_FOR_STMT:
        Return proc translate_for with stmt_node
    End If
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_WHILE_STMT:
        Return proc translate_while with stmt_node
    End If
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_SWITCH_STMT:
        Return proc translate_switch with stmt_node
    End If
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_TRY_STMT:
        Return proc translate_try with stmt_node
    End If
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_SPMD_STMT:
        Return proc translate_spmd with stmt_node
    End If
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_RETURN_STMT:
        Return proc hir_create_return from HIR
    End If
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_BREAK_STMT:
        Return proc hir_create_break from HIR
    End If
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_CONTINUE_STMT:
        Return proc hir_create_continue from HIR
    End If
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_GLOBAL_STMT:
        Return proc translate_scoped_decl with stmt_node, "matlab_global"
    End If
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_PERSISTENT_STMT:
        Return proc translate_scoped_decl with stmt_node, "matlab_persistent"
    End If
    If stmt_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_EXPR_STMT:
        Let expr_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with stmt_node, 0
        Let hir_expr be proc translate_expression with expr_child
        Return proc hir_create_expression_statement from HIR with hir_expr
    End If

    Note: Fallback: treat a bare expression node as an expression statement
    Let hir_fallback be proc translate_expression with stmt_node
    Return proc hir_create_expression_statement from HIR with hir_fallback
End Process

@Reasoning:
Wraps a MATLAB statement list (MATLAB_SCRIPT used as a block) into an HIR
block, translating each child statement in order.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_block" takes block_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir_block be proc hir_create_block from HIR
    Let count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with block_node
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let stmt be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with block_node, i
        Let hir_stmt be proc translate_statement with stmt
        If hir_stmt is not equal to 0:
            proc hir_add_statement from HIR with hir_block, hir_stmt
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return hir_block
End Process

@Reasoning:
"lhs = rhs" lowers to an HIR simple assignment expression wrapped in an
expression statement. Both sides are arbitrary expressions so the indexing
and member-access emitters compose naturally for complex lvalues.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_assignment" takes assign_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let lhs_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with assign_node, 0
    Let hir_lhs be proc translate_expression with lhs_child

    Let rhs_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with assign_node, 1
    Let hir_rhs be proc translate_expression with rhs_child

    Let hir_assign be proc hir_create_assign_expr from HIR with hir_lhs, HIR.HIR_ASSIGN_SIMPLE, hir_rhs
    Return proc hir_create_expression_statement from HIR with hir_assign
End Process

@Reasoning:
The MATLAB parser flattens if/elseif/else into a single IF_STMT whose
children are (cond, then, [elseif-cond, then]..., [else-block]). This routine
rebuilds the nested HIR if-chain: the first cond/then pair becomes the
outer HIR if; each subsequent cond/then pair becomes a nested HIR if placed
in the previous if's else slot; a trailing odd child becomes the innermost
else block.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_if" takes if_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with if_node

    Let cond_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with if_node, 0
    Let hir_cond be proc translate_expression with cond_child
    Let then_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with if_node, 1
    Let hir_then be proc translate_statement with then_child

    Let hir_if be proc hir_create_if from HIR
    proc hir_set_if_condition from HIR with hir_if, hir_cond
    proc hir_set_if_then from HIR with hir_if, hir_then

    Let result be hir_if
    Let current be hir_if
    Let idx be 2

    Note: Process trailing (elseif-cond, then) pairs and an optional else.
    Let remaining be count minus 2
    While remaining is greater than 0:
        If remaining is equal to 1:
            Note: Trailing else block
            Let else_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with if_node, idx
            Let hir_else be proc translate_statement with else_child
            proc hir_set_if_else from HIR with current, hir_else
            Set remaining to 0
        Otherwise:
            Note: An elseif pair becomes a nested HIR if in the else slot
            Let elseif_cond_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with if_node, idx
            Let elseif_hir_cond be proc translate_expression with elseif_cond_child
            Let elseif_then_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with if_node, idx plus 1
            Let elseif_hir_then be proc translate_statement with elseif_then_child

            Let nested_if be proc hir_create_if from HIR
            proc hir_set_if_condition from HIR with nested_if, elseif_hir_cond
            proc hir_set_if_then from HIR with nested_if, elseif_hir_then

            proc hir_set_if_else from HIR with current, nested_if
            Set current to nested_if
            Set idx to idx plus 2
            Set remaining to remaining minus 2
        End If
    End While

    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning:
"for var = iter ... end" lowers to HIR_FOR_IN with the loop variable name,
the iterable expression, and the body block. A parfor (signalled by a
trailing identifier child valued "parfor") is the same shape tagged
"matlab_parfor" so the backend re-emits the parfor keyword.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_for" takes for_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let var_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with for_node, 0
    Let var_name be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with var_child

    Let iter_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with for_node, 1
    Let hir_iter be proc translate_expression with iter_child

    Let body_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with for_node, 2
    Let hir_body be proc translate_statement with body_child

    Let hir_for be proc hir_create_for_in from HIR
    proc hir_set_for_in_variable from HIR with hir_for, var_name
    proc hir_set_for_in_iterable from HIR with hir_for, hir_iter
    proc hir_set_for_in_body from HIR with hir_for, hir_body

    Note: Detect parfor marker (4th child identifier valued "parfor")
    Let count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with for_node
    If count is greater than 3:
        Let marker be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with for_node, 3
        Let marker_value be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with marker
        Let is_parfor be proc string_equals from StringCore with marker_value, "parfor"
        If is_parfor is equal to 1:
            proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_for, "matlab_parfor", "1"
        End If
    End If

    Return hir_for
End Process

@Reasoning:
"while cond ... end" maps one-to-one onto HIR_WHILE with the condition and
body.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_while" takes while_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cond_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with while_node, 0
    Let hir_cond be proc translate_expression with cond_child

    Let body_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with while_node, 1
    Let hir_body be proc translate_statement with body_child

    Let hir_while be proc hir_create_while from HIR
    proc hir_set_while_condition from HIR with hir_while, hir_cond
    proc hir_set_while_body from HIR with hir_while, hir_body
    Return hir_while
End Process

@Reasoning:
"spmd ... end" is a block tagged "matlab_spmd" so the backend re-wraps it
in MATLAB's parallel spmd construct; structurally it is an ordinary block.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_spmd" takes spmd_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let body_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with spmd_node, 0
    Let hir_block be proc translate_statement with body_child
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_block, "matlab_spmd", "1"
    Return hir_block
End Process

@Reasoning:
MATLAB switch lowers to a chained if/elseif: the parser emits (expr, case_val,
case_body, ..., [otherwise_body]). Each case becomes "switch_expr == case_val"
guarding its body, nested through else slots; a trailing otherwise body is
the innermost else. This preserves switch semantics using only the HIR if
node which both ends of the pipeline already support, and is tagged
"matlab_switch" so the backend can re-emit the switch keyword form.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_switch" takes switch_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with switch_node
    Let expr_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with switch_node, 0

    Note: Build the chain. Remaining children after the scrutinee are
    Note: alternating case_val/case_body pairs with an optional trailing
    Note: otherwise body.
    Let head be 0
    Let current be 0
    Let idx be 1
    Let remaining be count minus 1

    While remaining is greater than 0:
        If remaining is equal to 1:
            Note: Trailing otherwise body
            Let otherwise_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with switch_node, idx
            Let hir_otherwise be proc translate_statement with otherwise_child
            If current is not equal to 0:
                proc hir_set_if_else from HIR with current, hir_otherwise
            End If
            Set remaining to 0
        Otherwise:
            Let case_val_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with switch_node, idx
            Let hir_case_val be proc translate_expression with case_val_child
            Let case_body_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with switch_node, idx plus 1
            Let hir_case_body be proc translate_statement with case_body_child

            Note: condition = (switch_expr == case_val); fresh scrutinee per arm
            Let hir_scrut be proc translate_expression with expr_child
            Let hir_eq be proc hir_create_binary_expr from HIR with HIR.HIR_OP_EQUAL, hir_scrut, hir_case_val

            Let arm_if be proc hir_create_if from HIR
            proc hir_set_if_condition from HIR with arm_if, hir_eq
            proc hir_set_if_then from HIR with arm_if, hir_case_body

            If head is equal to 0:
                Set head to arm_if
            Otherwise:
                proc hir_set_if_else from HIR with current, arm_if
            End If
            Set current to arm_if

            Set idx to idx plus 2
            Set remaining to remaining minus 2
        End If
    End While

    If head is equal to 0:
        Note: Switch with no cases - emit an empty block
        Return proc hir_create_block from HIR
    End If

    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with head, "matlab_switch", "1"
    Return head
End Process

@Reasoning:
"try ... catch (var)? ... end" lowers to a block tagged "matlab_try" that
contains the try-body statements followed by the catch-body statements,
with the optional exception variable recorded as "matlab_catch_var"
metadata. HIR's typed try node is not used here because the backend
re-emits MATLAB's single-catch form directly from this flat representation,
keeping producer and consumer in agreement on the simplest shape.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_try" takes try_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with try_node

    Let hir_block be proc hir_create_block from HIR
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_block, "matlab_try", "1"

    Note: First child is the try block.
    Let try_body_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with try_node, 0
    Let hir_try_body be proc translate_statement with try_body_child

    Let try_marker_lit be proc hir_create_string_literal from HIR with "try"
    Let try_marker be proc hir_create_expression_statement from HIR with try_marker_lit
    proc hir_add_statement from HIR with hir_block, try_marker
    proc hir_add_statement from HIR with hir_block, hir_try_body

    Note: Optional exception variable then catch block.
    Let catch_idx be 1
    If count is greater than 2:
        Let exc_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with try_node, 1
        Let exc_name be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with exc_child
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_block, "matlab_catch_var", exc_name
        Set catch_idx to 2
    End If

    If count is greater than catch_idx:
        Let catch_body_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with try_node, catch_idx
        Let hir_catch_body be proc translate_statement with catch_body_child
        Let catch_marker_lit be proc hir_create_string_literal from HIR with "catch"
        Let catch_marker be proc hir_create_expression_statement from HIR with catch_marker_lit
        proc hir_add_statement from HIR with hir_block, catch_marker
        proc hir_add_statement from HIR with hir_block, hir_catch_body
    End If

    Return hir_block
End Process

@Reasoning:
"global a b c" / "persistent a b c" lower to a block tagged with the given
scope kind whose statements are expression statements wrapping each declared
name; the declared names are also joined as "matlab_decl_names" metadata so
the backend re-emits the original "global a b c" line losslessly.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_scoped_decl" takes decl_node as Integer, tag as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir_block be proc hir_create_block from HIR
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_block, tag, "1"

    Let count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with decl_node
    Let joined be ""
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let var_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with decl_node, i
        Let var_name be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with var_child
        If i is greater than 0:
            Set joined to proc string_concat from StringPrim with joined, " "
        End If
        Set joined to proc string_concat from StringPrim with joined, var_name
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_block, "matlab_decl_names", joined
    Return hir_block
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: EXPRESSION TRANSLATION
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Expression dispatcher. Routes each MATLAB expression AST type to its HIR
translator. Unknown types fall back to an HIR identifier carrying the node's
value text so the round-trip never drops a subtree silently.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_expression" takes expr_node as Integer returns Integer:
    If expr_node is equal to 0:
        Return proc hir_create_identifier from HIR with ""
    End If

    Let expr_type be proc ast_node_type from MatlabParser with expr_node

    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_NUMBER_LITERAL:
        Return proc translate_number_literal with expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_STRING_LITERAL:
        Return proc translate_string_literal with expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_IDENTIFIER:
        Let id_name be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with expr_node
        Return proc hir_create_identifier from HIR with id_name
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_MATRIX_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_matrix_literal with expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_CELL_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_cell_literal with expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_BINARY_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_binary_expression with expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_UNARY_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_unary_expression with expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_CALL_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_call_expression with expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_INDEX_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_index_expression with expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_FIELD_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_field_expression with expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_DYNAMIC_FIELD_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_dynamic_field_expression with expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_COLON_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_colon_expression with expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_FUNC_HANDLE_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_function_handle with expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_LAMBDA_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_lambda with expr_node
    End If
    If expr_type is equal to MatlabParser.MATLAB_TRANSPOSE_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_transpose_expression with expr_node
    End If

    Let fallback_value be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with expr_node
    Return proc hir_create_identifier from HIR with fallback_value
End Process

@Reasoning:
A numeric literal is emitted as an HIR integer or float literal based on its
spelling (see matlab_number_is_float). The original spelling is stored as
the literal value so exponents and imaginary suffixes survive verbatim.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_number_literal" takes num_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let text be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with num_node
    Let is_float be proc matlab_number_is_float with text
    If is_float is equal to 1:
        Return proc hir_create_float_literal from HIR with text
    End If
    Return proc hir_create_int_literal from HIR with text
End Process

@Reasoning:
String and char literals both become HIR string literals (the underlying
immutable-text representation is shared).
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_string_literal" takes str_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let text be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with str_node
    Return proc hir_create_string_literal from HIR with text
End Process

@Reasoning:
Matrix literals "[a b; c d]" lower to an HIR list literal whose elements
are appended in row-major order. The list is tagged "matlab_matrix" and the
per-row element counts are joined into "matlab_matrix_rows" metadata so the
backend can restore the ';' row separators and original shape.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_matrix_literal" takes matrix_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir_list be proc hir_create_list_literal from HIR
    Let row_count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with matrix_node
    Let rows_meta be ""
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than row_count:
        Let row_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with matrix_node, i
        Let elem_count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with row_child
        If i is greater than 0:
            Set rows_meta to proc string_concat from StringPrim with rows_meta, ";"
        End If
        Let elem_count_text be proc matlab_int_text with elem_count
        Set rows_meta to proc string_concat from StringPrim with rows_meta, elem_count_text
        Let j be 0
        While j is less than elem_count:
            Let elem_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with row_child, j
            Let hir_elem be proc translate_expression with elem_child
            proc hir_add_list_element from HIR with hir_list, hir_elem
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_list, "matlab_matrix", "1"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_list, "matlab_matrix_rows", rows_meta
    Return hir_list
End Process

@Reasoning:
Renders a small non-negative integer as its decimal string. Used only to
record per-row element counts in matrix metadata; values are bounded by the
number of elements in a literal row, so a simple digit loop suffices.
@End Reasoning
Process called "matlab_int_text" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return "0"
    End If
    Let digits be ""
    Let n be value
    While n is greater than 0:
        Let quotient be n divided by 10
        Let truncated be quotient multiplied by 10
        Let digit be n minus truncated
        Let digit_char be digit plus 48
        Let digit_str be proc char_to_string from StringCore with digit_char
        Set digits to proc string_concat from StringPrim with digit_str, digits
        Set n to quotient
    End While
    Return digits
End Process

@Reasoning:
Cell arrays "{...}" lower to an HIR list literal tagged "matlab_cell" so the
backend re-emits braces and boxed heterogeneous elements.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_cell_literal" takes cell_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir_list be proc hir_create_list_literal from HIR
    Let count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with cell_node
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let elem_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with cell_node, i
        Let hir_elem be proc translate_expression with elem_child
        proc hir_add_list_element from HIR with hir_list, hir_elem
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_list, "matlab_cell", "1"
    Return hir_list
End Process

@Reasoning:
"op left right" becomes an HIR binary expression. The HIR op enum captures
the arithmetic/relational category for analysis passes, while the exact
MATLAB spelling (preserving '^', '.^', matrix-vs-elementwise) is stored as
"matlab_operator" metadata the backend reads back first. Element-wise
operators additionally set "matlab_elementwise".
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_binary_expression" takes binary_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let operator be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with binary_node
    Let left_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with binary_node, 0
    Let hir_left be proc translate_expression with left_child
    Let right_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with binary_node, 1
    Let hir_right be proc translate_expression with right_child

    Let hir_op be proc map_matlab_operator_to_hir with operator
    Let hir_binary be proc hir_create_binary_expr from HIR with hir_op, hir_left, hir_right
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_binary, "matlab_operator", operator

    Let is_elementwise be proc is_matlab_elementwise_operator with operator
    If is_elementwise is equal to 1:
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_binary, "matlab_elementwise", "1"
    End If

    Return hir_binary
End Process

@Reasoning:
Unary prefix "op operand" becomes an HIR unary expression; the exact MATLAB
spelling is preserved as metadata so the backend reproduces '~'/'-'/'+'.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_unary_expression" takes unary_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let operator be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with unary_node
    Let operand_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with unary_node, 0
    Let hir_operand be proc translate_expression with operand_child

    Let hir_op be proc map_matlab_unary_operator_to_hir with operator
    Let hir_unary be proc hir_create_unary_expr from HIR with hir_op, hir_operand
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_unary, "matlab_operator", operator
    Return hir_unary
End Process

@Reasoning:
A MATLAB call/index expression "base(args...)" lowers to an HIR call whose
callee is the base expression and whose positional arguments are each
translated child after the base. MATLAB call-vs-array-index ambiguity is
resolved later; here it is always emitted as a call (the most common form),
which the backend renders with parentheses.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_call_expression" takes call_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let base_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with call_node, 0
    Let hir_callee be proc translate_expression with base_child

    Let hir_call be proc hir_create_call_expr from HIR with hir_callee
    Let count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with call_node
    Let i be 1
    While i is less than count:
        Let arg_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with call_node, i
        Let hir_arg be proc translate_expression with arg_child
        proc hir_add_argument from HIR with hir_call, hir_arg
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return hir_call
End Process

@Reasoning:
A cell-indexing expression "base{idx...}" lowers to an HIR index expression
on the base with its first index, tagged "matlab_cell_indexing" so the
backend re-emits curly braces. Additional indices beyond the first are
preserved by chaining nested index expressions left to right.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_index_expression" takes index_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let base_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with index_node, 0
    Let hir_object be proc translate_expression with base_child

    Let count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with index_node
    Let result be hir_object
    Let i be 1
    While i is less than count:
        Let idx_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with index_node, i
        Let hir_index be proc translate_expression with idx_child
        Let hir_index_expr be proc hir_create_index_expr from HIR with result, hir_index
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_index_expr, "matlab_cell_indexing", "1"
        Set result to hir_index_expr
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning:
"obj.field" lowers to an HIR member expression: the object subtree plus the
static field name string read from the identifier child.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_field_expression" takes field_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let object_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with field_node, 0
    Let hir_object be proc translate_expression with object_child

    Let field_ident be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with field_node, 1
    Let field_name be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with field_ident

    Return proc hir_create_member_expr from HIR with hir_object, field_name
End Process

@Reasoning:
"obj.(expr)" computes the field name at runtime; it lowers to an HIR index
expression of the object by the field-name expression, tagged
"matlab_dynamic_field" so the backend re-emits the obj.(...) form.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_dynamic_field_expression" takes dyn_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let object_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with dyn_node, 0
    Let hir_object be proc translate_expression with object_child

    Let field_expr_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with dyn_node, 1
    Let hir_field_expr be proc translate_expression with field_expr_child

    Let hir_index be proc hir_create_index_expr from HIR with hir_object, hir_field_expr
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_index, "matlab_dynamic_field", "1"
    Return hir_index
End Process

@Reasoning:
The colon operator has three forms: bare ":" (0 children) becomes an
identifier ":" tagged "matlab_colon_all"; "start:end" (2 children) and
"start:step:end" (3 children) become HIR index expressions chaining the
arms with "matlab_range" metadata so the backend reconstructs the colon
spelling. Using member/index nodes keeps producer and consumer on shared
node kinds without needing a dedicated HIR range node.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_colon_expression" takes colon_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with colon_node

    If count is equal to 0:
        Let colon_all be proc hir_create_identifier from HIR with ":"
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with colon_all, "matlab_colon_all", "1"
        Return colon_all
    End If

    If count is equal to 2:
        Let start_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with colon_node, 0
        Let hir_start be proc translate_expression with start_child
        Let end_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with colon_node, 1
        Let hir_end be proc translate_expression with end_child
        Let hir_range be proc hir_create_index_expr from HIR with hir_start, hir_end
        proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_range, "matlab_range", "2"
        Return hir_range
    End If

    Note: count == 3 -> start:step:end
    Let s_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with colon_node, 0
    Let hir_s be proc translate_expression with s_child
    Let step_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with colon_node, 1
    Let hir_step be proc translate_expression with step_child
    Let e_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with colon_node, 2
    Let hir_e be proc translate_expression with e_child

    Let inner be proc hir_create_index_expr from HIR with hir_s, hir_step
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with inner, "matlab_range_inner", "1"
    Let outer be proc hir_create_index_expr from HIR with inner, hir_e
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with outer, "matlab_range", "3"
    Return outer
End Process

@Reasoning:
"@name" becomes an HIR identifier carrying the function name tagged
"matlab_func_handle" so the backend re-prepends '@'.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_function_handle" takes handle_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let func_name be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with handle_node
    Let hir_id be proc hir_create_identifier from HIR with func_name
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_id, "matlab_func_handle", "1"
    Return hir_id
End Process

@Reasoning:
"@(params) body" becomes an HIR call expression whose callee identifier is
the synthetic "@" marker tagged "matlab_lambda"; the parameter names are
joined into "matlab_lambda_params" metadata and the single body expression
is added as the call's sole argument so the backend reconstructs the
"@(a, b) expr" anonymous-function spelling.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_lambda" takes lambda_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let params_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with lambda_node, 0

    Let joined be ""
    Let param_count be proc ast_node_child_count from MatlabParser with params_child
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than param_count:
        Let param_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with params_child, i
        Let param_name be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with param_child
        If i is greater than 0:
            Set joined to proc string_concat from StringPrim with joined, ", "
        End If
        Set joined to proc string_concat from StringPrim with joined, param_name
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Let marker be proc hir_create_identifier from HIR with "@lambda"
    Let hir_call be proc hir_create_call_expr from HIR with marker
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_call, "matlab_lambda", "1"
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_call, "matlab_lambda_params", joined

    Let body_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with lambda_node, 1
    Let hir_body be proc translate_expression with body_child
    proc hir_add_argument from HIR with hir_call, hir_body

    Return hir_call
End Process

@Reasoning:
"'" and ".'" transpose lower to an HIR unary expression with the original
spelling preserved as "matlab_transpose" metadata so the backend re-emits
the suffix operator in the correct (conjugate vs plain) form.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_transpose_expression" takes transpose_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let spelling be proc ast_node_value from MatlabParser with transpose_node
    Let operand_child be proc ast_node_child from MatlabParser with transpose_node, 0
    Let hir_operand be proc translate_expression with operand_child

    Let hir_unary be proc hir_create_unary_expr from HIR with HIR.HIR_OP_NEGATE, hir_operand
    proc hir_set_metadata from HIR with hir_unary, "matlab_transpose", spelling
    Return hir_unary
End Process

Note: ===================================================================
Note: PUBLIC SOURCE FACADE
Note: ===================================================================

@Reasoning:
Public single-arg facade invoked by the translation dispatcher's
LANG_MATLAB arm. Wires the full source -> HIR pipeline: the MATLAB lexer
and parser build the AST, and translate_matlab_to_hir lowers it to typed
HIR. The parser pulls tokens lazily from the lexer, so no separate tokenize
phase is required. Short-circuits to 0 on a null AST.
@End Reasoning
Process called "matlab_to_hir_from_source" takes source_code as Integer returns Integer:
    Let lexer be proc matlab_lexer_create from MatlabLexer with source_code
    Let parser be proc matlab_parser_create from MatlabParser with lexer
    Let ast be proc parse_program from MatlabParser with parser
    If ast is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc translate_matlab_to_hir with ast
End Process
